      "content": "i get that, but my coach is saying that one of those is basically just a workaround for people who don't care about laws, while the other is a fundamental human right that can't be ignored. if u had to pick a starting point for a winning debate, wouldn't it make more sense to ground it in the human rights side since that feels more \"objectively\" right on a global scale?",
